text: Thryptomene calciola is a shrub species in the family Myrtaceae that is endemic to Western Australia. The shrub is found in a small area in the Mid West region of Western Australia near Northampton where it grows in sandy soils. ==References== calciola Category:Endemic flora of Western Australia Category:Endangered flora of Australia Category:Rosids of Western Australia Category:Plants described in 2014
title: Thryptomene calciola
